          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Photoparticles were  registered  in  the  interval of",
                " angles from 20 to 120 degrees with  respect  to  the",
                " g-quanta  beam direction.  To identify the particles",
                " the orientation of their tracks in the emulsions was",
                " measured besides the ranges."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The errors given for cross section values are",
                " statistical."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The spectra and angular distribution of  photoprotons",
                " from  the  reaction  Be-9(g,p) are investigated with",
                " the aid of the nuclear  photoplates  in  a  magnetic",
                " field  and  the reaction cross section was obtained.",
                " Additionally    the    reaction    Be-9(g,d)     was",
                " investigated.  a  comparatively  high  ratio  of the",
                " yield of deuterons to that of protons  (Y(d)/Y(p)  =",
                " 0.20(0.10)  at  Ep  >  3.7 MeV and Ed < 14,2 MeV) is",
                " measured.  The  cross  sections  for  the  reactions",
                " accompanied  by  deuteron emission were estimated to",
                " account for 6 to 7%  of the total cross section  for",
                " the  absorption  of g-quanta with energies from 16.7",
                " to 35.0 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
